es/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>   Arunhakk Igatahayirbaal<br>   54 Beastlord<br>   Luclin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/udeamereq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DeamerEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Playful Cub</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF9933>(9/26/02 3:26:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   It may be wonderful for some....</span><hr size=1> 1.  To be honest, I don't think I've had that happen to me enough to justify having it memmed.  Once a month just isn't worth it.  I think I've died maybe 3 times between the levels of 30 and 53.  <br><br>2.  Let me guess, your main is a necro?  Fear kiting is not a reliable beastlord strategy, stick with what works.  This has been a problem since BL's came about, people try to teach new dogs old tricks....there are plenty of new tricks that work just as good, if not better.  <br><br>3.  Again, this does not happen enough to keep it memmed.  I just cannot justify keeping a spell memmed, 'just in case'.  <br><br>4.  As far as taunt is concerned, I dont' know what others do, but I was in a group with 2 wizards, both using tears of druzzil at the same time, they never once got aggro from my warder.  <br><br>5.  Again, this is another 'just in case' scenario.  Like I said, I have no problem with taunt.  <br><br>Just so everyone knows what I keep handy:<br><br>Slot 1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> et heal (buffer for complete heal only)<br>Slot 2:Spirit of Wolf (no need for explanation)<br>Slot 3:Venom of the Snake (if you can find a pathing exploit, you can solo with this spell alone)<br>Slot 4:Sha's Lathargy (slower mob, easier to cast when getting pounded on)<br>Slot 5:Utiliy spells(EB, Lev, Crack, etc...)<br>Slot 6:Pet Haste  (this spell makes or breaks the pet)<br>Slot 7:Pet Proc buff  (no need for explanation)<br>Slot 8:Pet lvl buff (also used as complete heal)<br><br>The only slot other than 5 that I will switch stuff out is slot 2, and only if I'm in a dungeon where I cannot cast it, which is actually pretty rare for me.  <br><br>I'm not saying FoL is useless, but it's definetely not going to be in my starting line-up when soloing or in a typical group.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/utipop.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tipop</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><HR color=#CC3300><font color=#330066><CENTER><b><font color=#000000 face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif size=1>Beast Overlord Kraggan</font></b> </CENTER></font><HR color=#CC3300></span><br>  Posts: 1676<br> <font color=#FF9933>(9/26/02 5:15:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.telocity.com/~Tipop2000/minimark.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: It may be wonderful for some....</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 1. Life-saver when soloing<br><br>1. To be honest, I don't think I've had that happen to me enough to justify having it memmed.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>You've never had the warder die on you?  You've never had a need to get a mob off long enough to summon?  You've never been snared by a mob and unable to run?<br><br>Hat's off to ya.  You're a better player than I.<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 2. Ghetto fear spell<br><br>2. Let m